    <note>Su(1) Zhang [11588] Renming, p. 1780 and ancestor Jian's [11586] documentation. According to Su Xun, WJ, 13.5a, Zhang's descendants lived in Zhaojun and that the Zhaojun Su considered him their penultimate (zong) ancestor, whereas the Fufeng Su consider Jian to be their penultimate ancestor (zong). This is confirmed in the Tang zaixiang genealogical tables, which make Zhang's descendant, Weidao [19214] (q.v.), a zaixiang of Wu(6) Zitian [24637], the first Zhaojun Su. However, other descendants of Zhang remain as Fufeng Su. I am making a son of Zhang, Su C [19213], as the person who moved to Zhaojun and his descendants to be Zhaojun Su, whereas other descendants of Zhang clearly remained Fufeng Su. Su(1) Xun [3762] (q.v.) cannot trace his own family beyong his great great grandfather, Jin [19216], a descendant of Weidao according to the collective memory of the lineage.</note>
